  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Peel and chop half your<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>shallots</strong> into wedges, then slice the <strong>remaining shallot[s]</strong> finely</p><p>Chop your <strong>potatoes[s]</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Peel then chop your <strong>sweet potato[s]</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Top, tail and slice your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> at an angle</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1684845449905-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1684845449905-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1684845449905-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1684845449905-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1684845449905-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>shallot wedges</strong>, <strong>sliced carrot</strong> and all the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a generous grind of <strong>black</strong> <strong>pepper </strong>and<strong> </strong>give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for an initial 20 min or until the potatoes have started to brown</p><p>Boil a kettle</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1684845453595-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1684845453595-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1684845453595-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1684845453595-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1684845453595-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the potatoes are in the oven, peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Cut half your <strong>red chilli[es]</strong> into rounds</p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining chilli</strong> in half, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop finely</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1684845460020-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1684845460020-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1684845460020-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1684845460020-x1000.jpg",
