            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1684845464386-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your<strong> coconut cream </strong>and <strong>red Thai</strong> <strong>curry paste</strong> with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span><strong> sugar</strong> in 150ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [200ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Add your<strong> fish sauce</strong>, <strong>chopped chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and<strong> ginger</strong> and stir everything together – this is your<strong> red Thai curry stock</strong></p><p>Trim, then chop your <strong>green beans</strong> in half</p><p>Crush your <strong>cardamom pods</strong> open by squashing them with the side of a knife</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1684845467863-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1684845467863-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1684845467863-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1684845467863-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1684845467863-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Remove the tray from the oven and spoon away any excess oil</p><p>Add the <strong>meatballs</strong>, <strong>halved</strong> <strong>green beans</strong>, <strong>cardamom pods </strong>and<strong> lime leaves</strong> to the tray and pour the<strong> red Thai curry stock </strong>over everything</p><p>Return the tray to the oven for 15 min further or until the meatballs are cooked through (no pink meat!) and the sauce is thick and rich – this is your<strong> red Thai-style beef meatball bake</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1684845471153-x200.jpg",
